      • updateRelationIds

        void updateRelationIds()
                throws SecurityException,
                       NoSuchMethodException,
                       IllegalArgumentException,
                       IllegalAccessException,
                       InvocationTargetException,
                       NoSuchFieldException
        This method is only useful for the persistence of IGeneObj relations: as it is not possible to persist interface relations (that are everywhere in the GeneObj), the ids are stored in a private field for each relation; this method fills the id field with the ids of the objects that are actually related. The method uses the EncodedRelation annotation to find the relations to update in this.
        Throws:
        SecurityException

      • fillRelationsFromIds

        void fillRelationsFromIds()
                   throws IllegalArgumentException,
                          IllegalAccessException,
                          InvocationTargetException,
                          SecurityException,
                          NoSuchFieldException,
                          NoSuchMethodException
        This method is the opposite of updateRelationIds() in the persistence management. It fills the relations of this with other IGeneObj objects using the id collection fields annotated by EncodedRelation. The setters of the relations are used by reflection and the objects are queried using their ids and their class, encoded in the annotation fields.
        Throws:
        InvocationTargetException
        IllegalAccessException
        IllegalArgumentException
        NoSuchFieldException
        SecurityException
        NoSuchMethodException

      • restoreGeoxObjects

        void restoreGeoxObjects()
        This method is only useful for the persistence of IGeneObj. To avoid using EJB with GeOxygene objects, the GeOxygene object related to a IGeneObj object is transient, so it has to be restored. It is restored using this geometry and attributes. The GeOxygene object relations are not restored by this method but by restoreGeoxRelations().

      • restoreGeoxRelations

        void restoreGeoxRelations()
        This method is only useful for the persistence of IGeneObj.To avoid using EJB with GeOxygene objects, the GeOxygene object related to a IGeneObj object is transient, so it has to be restored. The standard restoration is carried out by restoreGeoxObjects() but the relations are restored afterwards by this method, once all the GeOxygene objects have been restored.
